    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-07-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="518"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Count Wydenbruck</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-07-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 11, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: I thank you for your obliging
                    communication of the 9th instant, (8th.) As soon as the answer to Captain Roe’s
                    application shall be known to you, may I hope that you may have the goodness to
                    have it telegraphed to me, in order that my court may be informed of its tenor
                    without loss of time ?</p>
                <p>I have the honor to remain, Mr. Secretary of State, with the highest
                    consideration, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WYDENBRUCK.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
